that I don’t know what it means; it means

175
00:16:28,199 --> 00:16:32,670
grandeur, or nature, or anything, or you all
people.

176
00:16:32,670 --> 00:16:35,160
I enjoy everything of it.

177
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:39,269
So for Me there’s no need for you to.

178
00:16:39,269 --> 00:16:45,709
Now as he said that those people came, three
of them ? Brahma, Vishnu, Mahesha ? to give

179
00:16:45,709 --> 00:16:47,300
presents to Christ.

180
00:16:47,300 --> 00:16:50,180
Yes, they did.

181
00:16:50,180 --> 00:16:52,509
And you have given Me, too.

182
00:16:52,509 --> 00:16:58,130
But now I think it’s better that you people
reduce some quantity at least.

183
00:16:58,130 --> 00:17:03,769
I’ll be very thankful that if something
could be done like that, and from next year

184
00:17:03,769 --> 00:17:08,200
we should try to make it less and less and
less.

185
00:17:08,200 --> 00:17:15,050
Because it’s very sweet of you to have given
Me all those things, because I enjoyed them,

186
00:17:15,050 --> 00:17:21,200
they are beautiful things, and when I see
them I remember your good heart.

187
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:28,670
But you know that Mother is too simple and
though I can create all kinds of things, as

188
00:17:28,670 --> 00:17:32,850
far as I am concerned I am too simple.

189
00:17:32,850 --> 00:17:33,850
And also Mr.

190
00:17:33,850 --> 00:17:38,080
Shrivastava so many times, says also, “You’ve
got so many saris but you’ll go on with

191
00:17:38,080 --> 00:17:40,550
Your white sari all the time."

192
00:17:40,550 --> 00:17:51,300
The reason is, you see, a simple personality
can only create beautiful things.

193
00:17:51,300 --> 00:18:02,210
A simple heart can only create nice things,
because simplicity at the simple level is

194
00:18:02,210 --> 00:18:03,600
so simple.

195
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:10,380
Like you are made of seven chakras, seven
chakras, then the permutations of these seven

196
00:18:10,380 --> 00:18:11,790
chakras, that’s all.

197
00:18:11,790 --> 00:18:17,250
But supposing you start from outside then
you’ll have to go to medical science or

198
00:18:17,250 --> 00:18:20,020
you’ll have to go to another complicated
thing.

199
00:18:20,020 --> 00:18:22,050
But basically, fundamentally, it’s too simple.

200
00:18:22,050 --> 00:18:28,490
That’s why Sahaja Yoga is very simple, because
we are dealing with the fundamental things.

201
00:18:28,490 --> 00:18:35,390
So fundamentally, if you are simple then everything
that you do is just a combination and permutation

202
00:18:35,390 --> 00:18:42,050
of all these things, and all these things
when they are put together they make such

203
00:18:42,050 --> 00:18:43,050
beautiful things.

204
00:18:43,050 --> 00:18:48,640
For example, as I have told you once I was
travelling and we went to a place called Palitana

205
00:18:48,640 --> 00:18:52,250
known to be a very beautiful, beautifully
carved place.

206
00:18:52,250 --> 00:18:57,460
And we had to walk, I don’t know, for three
miles at least, climbing up or something like

207
00:18:57,460 --> 00:18:58,460
that.

208
00:18:58,460 --> 00:19:00,930
With Me was My daughter and My son-in-law.

209
00:19:00,930 --> 00:19:03,050
Went up and there was a little temple.

210
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:04,810
They wanted to rest.

211
00:19:04,810 --> 00:19:07,880
And also we laid down ourselves there.

212
00:19:07,880 --> 00:19:14,460
And as soon as I saw all these beautiful elephants
were there, so I told My son-in-law, “Look

213
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:15,690
at these elephants.

214
00:19:15,690 --> 00:19:18,150
All their tails are twisted differently."

215
00:19:18,150 --> 00:19:21,300
He said, “Mummy, we are so fed up.

216
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:26,240
How do you have energy to see the tails?”

217
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:31,080
I said, “Because I see the tails I don’t
feel tired.

218
00:19:31,080 --> 00:19:32,540
That’s the point.

219
00:19:32,540 --> 00:19:35,160
Because I see the beauty of these tails, I
— ”.

220
00:19:35,160 --> 00:19:39,030
So you see, even in simple things there is
so much of beauty.

221
00:19:39,030 --> 00:19:50,750
In very, very ordinary persons you’ll find
that they have a very beautiful things and

