00:19:50,750 --> 00:20:01,930
very nice way of saying things, very simple
talks of children like that, it’s so simple,

223
00:20:01,930 --> 00:20:06,120
so straightforward, and whatever they say
it’s so deep.

224
00:20:06,120 --> 00:20:12,210
So whatever is deep is simple, but when it
is expressed outside it can have lots of permutations

225
00:20:12,210 --> 00:20:18,660
and combinations and it can work out in a
beautiful way.

226
00:20:18,660 --> 00:20:19,700
I must tell you, I had no strain in making
this house, nothing.

227
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:25,741
I was not bothered at all.

228
00:20:25,741 --> 00:20:30,030
I found everything so easily; I brought it
here, put it down here, I never even thought

229
00:20:30,030 --> 00:20:31,030
there’s strain or anything.

230
00:20:31,030 --> 00:20:32,030
Everybody says, “What a concept."

231
00:20:32,030 --> 00:20:33,390
But I never conceived anything.

232
00:20:33,390 --> 00:20:36,210
I mean, I just don’t know.

233
00:20:36,210 --> 00:20:40,430
What is a concept is there; I just told, “To
Me is nothing great."

234
00:20:40,430 --> 00:20:45,370
The whole world is there for us to see and
to be fascinated.

235
00:20:45,370 --> 00:20:52,960
But behind all that, all this world and everything
is created with the very little, simple idea

236
00:20:52,960 --> 00:21:00,380
of God, that you all have to enter into the
Kingdom of God.

237
00:21:00,380 --> 00:21:04,070
That’s all; such a simple idea.

238
00:21:04,070 --> 00:21:09,110
So He’s created such a beautiful world,
then he created all kinds of things to bring

239
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:15,530
you to the human level, and now just simple
thing is to enter into the Kingdom of God.

240
00:21:15,530 --> 00:21:20,550
You should not complicate yourself too much
and once you do that you will be surprised

241
00:21:20,550 --> 00:21:25,200
how beautifully you will be able to produce.

242
00:21:25,200 --> 00:21:28,310
Even some artists were extremely simple by
nature.

243
00:21:28,310 --> 00:21:36,010
Like Ravi Shankar, you know, and his guru,
he has got Alla Raka and Ali Akbar; all these

244
00:21:36,010 --> 00:21:37,210
were his disciples.

245
00:21:37,210 --> 00:21:39,824
Such a great genius man, such a simple man,
I tell you.

246
00:21:39,824 --> 00:21:41,180
And he knew Me very well.

247
00:21:41,180 --> 00:21:44,890
He used to call Me “Ma”; he used to call
Me “Mother” from the very beginning.

248
00:21:44,890 --> 00:21:57,470
And one day he brought one little deer, a
baby deer, brought it to Me.

249
00:21:57,470 --> 00:21:59,300
I said, “What’s the matter?”

250
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:03,140
He said, “See, this deer was crying too
much.

251
00:22:03,140 --> 00:22:04,270
So I brought it to You."

252
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:06,350
But I said, “For, why for Me?”

253
00:22:06,350 --> 00:22:09,340
“So, You see, he will feel the love of his
Mother.

254
00:22:09,340 --> 00:22:11,160
So You just caress him."

255
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:15,940
Imagine, such a great artist coming like a
little baby to Me, making that.

256
00:22:15,940 --> 00:22:17,750
I was so surprised at him.

257
00:22:17,750 --> 00:22:20,050
Look at him; such a simple man.

258
00:22:20,050 --> 00:22:22,850
He’s doing that.

259
00:22:22,850 --> 00:22:28,690
And you see, if you see the children when
they love, how genuine they are, how they

260
00:22:28,690 --> 00:22:29,690
work it out.

261
00:22:29,690 --> 00:22:30,840
The same place there was a child.

262
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:32,720
He was very fond of Me.

263
00:22:32,720 --> 00:22:43,420
And one day he decided to bring some pumpkins
for Me.

264
00:22:43,420 --> 00:22:46,050
So he brought one to Me.

265
00:22:46,050 --> 00:22:47,660
I saw him bringing in the thing.

266
00:22:47,660 --> 00:22:49,510
He said, “All right, just wait."

267
00:22:49,510 --> 00:22:54,190
Then there was, he went back, and there was
another one kept little further.

268
00:22:54,190 --> 00:22:55,590
He brought that.

269
00:22:55,590 --> 00:22:59,710
He had put nine of them in different places.

270
00:22:59,710 --> 00:23:01,900
One by one he was bringing them.

271
00:23:01,900 --> 00:23:04,340
He brought nine pumpkins to give Me.

272
00:23:04,340 --> 00:23:05,340
So sweet.

273
00:23:05,340 --> 00:23:07,980
But I said, “Why did you bring nine?”

274
00:23:07,980 --> 00:23:13,470
“Because I don’t know which one you like
so I brought all of them."

275
00:23:13,470 --> 00:23:17,770
So simple and so touching; I mean, just [touch/touches/tears/turns]
your heart.

276
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:19,530
So we have to be simple people.

277
00:23:19,530 --> 00:23:26,030
We have to talk to each other in a simple
way, not in a complicated way, in a very simple,

278
00:23:26,030 --> 00:23:27,120
sweet manner.

279
00:23:27,120 --> 00:23:31,600
That’s how we are going to create a beautiful
world.

280
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:38,750
So I would request all of you to be very kindly
and very gentle with each other, especially

281
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:42,130
for the newly marrying couples.

282
00:23:42,130 --> 00:23:45,280
Try to be nice.

283
00:23:45,280 --> 00:23:48,150
Nobody is going to dominate you if you are
nice.

284
00:23:48,150 --> 00:23:50,760
It’s only you dominate yourself.

285
00:23:50,760 --> 00:23:54,540
And don’t try to control your husbands or
your wives.

286
00:23:54,540 --> 00:23:55,540
Let them be.

287
00:23:55,540 --> 00:23:57,530
Let them enjoy their freedom.

288
00:23:57,530 --> 00:23:59,390
They are not going to do anything wrong.

289
00:23:59,390 --> 00:24:03,870
So some people try to control too much and
there are problems.

290
00:24:03,870 --> 00:24:07,610
So please do not try to control like, “If
I am keeping it here, they’ll keep it there."

291
00:24:07,610 --> 00:24:08,750
There’s no need.

292
00:24:08,750 --> 00:24:09,750
Let it be.

293
00:24:09,750 --> 00:24:12,370
Doesn’t matter; nothing so serious.

294
00:24:12,370 --> 00:24:16,840
But on small, small things, I’ve seen, such
marriages fizzle out.

295
00:24:16,840 --> 00:24:19,470
And it is absolutely wrong.

296
00:24:19,470 --> 00:24:22,110
So for marriages today, it’s a very auspicious
day.

297
00:24:22,110 --> 00:24:25,670
So many people have been engaged to be married.

298
00:24:25,670 --> 00:24:30,660
But one thing you must remember, that you
should not lose your connection with joy.

299
00:24:30,660 --> 00:24:31,840
It’s stupidity.

300
00:24:31,840 --> 00:24:36,660
When two nice birds are together they should
chirp and laugh and enjoy.

301
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:43,790
Instead of that, if they start pricking each
other, what should we call them?

302
00:24:43,790 --> 00:24:46,890
So today it’s a great joy for Me.

303
00:24:46,890 --> 00:24:51,110
So many people are engaged and are going to
get married.

304
00:24:51,110 --> 00:24:55,460
But now, understand your responsibility that
nothing is to be done.

305
00:24:55,460 --> 00:24:58,060
You have to be just sahaj; don’t have to
do anything.

306
00:24:58,060 --> 00:24:59,310
“We are working out."

307
00:24:59,310 --> 00:25:02,200
You cannot work out marriage; you cannot work
out.

308
00:25:02,200 --> 00:25:08,470
Just know about your husband or about your
wife and just try to enjoy whatever they are.

309
00:25:08,470 --> 00:25:15,100
I mean, I do enjoy that way about My husband,
so many things which may sound little queer

310
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,290
to people, but I enjoy it.

311
00:25:16,290 --> 00:25:20,720
Because I know that’s a nice thing about
our human beings that they have varieties

312
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:24,600
and they have little, different angles to
themselves.

313
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:28,340
And these angles are to be enjoyed and to
be appreciated.

314
00:25:28,340 --> 00:25:31,030
If you can do that, then you will never fight.

315
00:25:31,030 --> 00:25:35,450
Because two persons cannot be alike; even
two leaves are not alike.

316
00:25:35,450 --> 00:25:37,240
So you should enjoy.

317
00:25:37,240 --> 00:25:43,400
Everybody has some sort of a super quality
thing or whatever it is or maybe some angle.

318
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:45,240
Just enjoy that angle.

319
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:49,710
You don’t have that; so let him have at
least, or let her have that.

320
00:25:49,710 --> 00:25:53,950
So today, special day is that so many marriages
have been fixed out.

321
00:25:53,950 --> 00:25:58,220
I don’t know how many ? he has not told
Me yet the number ? but quite a lot have been

322
00:25:58,220 --> 00:25:59,220
fixed.

323
00:25:59,220 --> 00:26:00,220
Sahaja yogi: Fifty.

324
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:02,360
Shri Mataji: Fifty have been already fixed.

325
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:03,360
All right.

326
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:09,360
So now it’s a very big number and will be
more by the time we reach Ganapatipule.

327
00:26:09,360 --> 00:26:12,110
So let us not create problems out of this.

328
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:13,150
You don’t have to sit down.

329
00:26:13,150 --> 00:26:17,920
I have seen after marriage they start thinking,
“What, what do you think about him?”

330
00:26:17,920 --> 00:26:20,220
It’s like after realization you start thinking.

331
00:26:20,220 --> 00:26:23,420
Once you are married, you are not to think
then accept.

332
00:26:23,420 --> 00:26:24,460
Before marriage you think.

333
00:26:24,460 --> 00:26:27,510
What’s the use of thinking after marriage?

334
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:32,650
It’s a very common thing.

335
00:26:32,650 --> 00:26:33,980
After marriage they start thinking.

336
00:26:33,980 --> 00:26:36,060
Then, after marriage you enjoy.

337
00:26:36,060 --> 00:26:38,290
After cooking the food you eat the food.

338
00:26:38,290 --> 00:26:42,750
Or after the food has been served then you
start thinking about it.

339
00:26:42,750 --> 00:26:43,750
It’s absurd.

340
00:26:43,750 --> 00:26:48,680
So this is a very common failing we have had
so far.

341
00:26:48,680 --> 00:26:52,840
I would like to tell you first of all, you
think before getting married and after getting

342
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:54,620
married you carry on.

343
00:26:54,620 --> 00:26:55,740
And don’t try to control.

344
00:26:55,740 --> 00:26:57,900
Don’t try to dictate.

345
00:26:57,900 --> 00:26:59,600
Try to be nice and sweet.

346
00:26:59,600 --> 00:27:04,230
You don’t have to go out of the way, but
be normal and it will all work out.

347
00:27:04,230 --> 00:27:09,710
May God bless you all, specially all the girls
and boys who have been engaged.

348
00:27:09,710 --> 00:27:14,960
I bless you from My heart, and enjoy each
other; that’s the main point.

349
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:16,530
So thank you very much.

350
00:27:16,530 --> 00:27:16,540
Thank you.

